/*
  Workspace blocks guide: flyout-style labels only (no internal block type ids in the first column).
*/

update public.lms_learning_guides
set body_html = $body$<p>This reference matches the <strong>toolbox categories and colors</strong> in the Ollie workspace (left flyout). Each row shows how the block reads in the toolbox, what it does, and typical ways to use it. Hat blocks start a script; other blocks stack below them.</p><h2><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> Events</h2><p>Events decide <strong>when</strong> a script runs. Every stack needs a hat block at the top.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>When … clicked</strong></td><td>Runs the script once when the program starts (like the green flag).</td><td>Place at the top of a stack. Use one main start script per sprite, or several stacks that all respond to start.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>When … key pressed</strong></td><td>Runs when the learner presses a chosen key.</td><td>Pick the key from the menu. Use for movement, jumping, or resetting a mini-game.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>When stage clicked</strong></td><td>Runs when the stage (background) is clicked.</td><td>Good for “click to begin” or tapping targets on the backdrop.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>When scene switches to …</strong></td><td>Runs when the scene switches to a specific backdrop.</td><td>Chain level flow: when “Level 2” backdrop appears, reset positions or show a message.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>When I receive …</strong></td><td>Runs when a named message is received.</td><td>Pair with the <strong>Broadcast …</strong> block so sprites coordinate (score change, game over, next phase).</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Broadcast …</strong></td><td>Sends a named message to all sprites (does not wait).</td><td>Use when listeners should run in parallel. Name messages clearly (e.g. <code>game-over</code>).</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Broadcast … and wait</strong></td><td>Sends a message and waits until all receiving scripts finish.</td><td>Use when order matters: cutscene finished, then start the next dialog.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> Motion</h2><p>Motion blocks move and turn the <strong>active sprite</strong> on the stage.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Move … steps</strong></td><td>Moves the sprite forward in the direction it is facing.</td><td>Inside loops or after turns; use numbers for how far to step.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Turn … degrees</strong></td><td>Turns the sprite by a number of degrees.</td><td>Positive vs negative angles for left/right feel; combine with move for paths.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Turn left … degrees</strong></td><td>Turns the sprite left by a fixed amount from the menu.</td><td>Quick turns for younger learners without typing degrees.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Turn right … degrees</strong></td><td>Turns the sprite right by a fixed amount from the menu.</td><td>Pair with forward moves for simple mazes and driving games.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Point in direction …</strong></td><td>Sets the sprite’s heading to a compass angle (0–360).</td><td>0 often points right; 90 up—use for snapping to exact directions.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Point towards …</strong></td><td>Points the sprite toward another sprite or target.</td><td>Chase behaviors, aiming projectiles, or following a friend character.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Set point offset sideways … %</strong></td><td>Points toward the aim/cursor-style target used in Ollie lessons.</td><td>Use when gameplay uses the aim reticle instead of another sprite.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Go to x: … y: … (−100–100)</strong></td><td>Teleports the sprite to exact x and y coordinates.</td><td>Reset position, snap to grid, or jump between waypoints.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Go to …</strong></td><td>Teleports the sprite to another sprite’s position.</td><td>Follow the leader, swap places, or spawn at a marker sprite.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Change x by …</strong></td><td>Slides the sprite left/right by adding to x.</td><td>Smooth sideways motion; put in a loop for continuous drift.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Change y by …</strong></td><td>Slides the sprite up/down by adding to y.</td><td>Jump arcs (with waits), gravity-style motion, or bouncing.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>Glide … secs to x: … y: …</strong></td><td>Smoothly moves to a position over a duration.</td><td>Animations, sliding doors, tween-style entrances.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#59C059">■</span> <strong>If on edge, bounce</strong></td><td>If touching the edge of the stage, bounce instead of leaving the screen.</td><td>Keep characters on screen in free-movement games.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> Looks</h2><p>Looks control what the sprite <strong>says, wears, and how big</strong> it is.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Say … for … seconds</strong></td><td>Shows a speech bubble with fixed text for a duration.</td><td>Dialog, hints, or story beats—stack multiple says in order.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Say … for … seconds</strong></td><td>Shows a speech bubble with a value (number or text from a block).</td><td>Scores, timers, or variable values the player should read.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Think … for … seconds</strong></td><td>Shows a thought bubble instead of speech.</td><td>Jokes, inner monologue, or “Hmm…” moments.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Set speech bubble color to …</strong></td><td>Changes speech/thought bubble styling.</td><td>Match character mood or improve contrast on busy backdrops.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Switch costume to …</strong></td><td>Switches to a costume chosen from the dropdown.</td><td>Walk cycles, damage states, power-ups—swap art without new sprites.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Next costume</strong></td><td>Advances to the next costume in the list.</td><td>Simple animation by looping next costume with a short wait.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Show</strong></td><td>Makes the sprite visible.</td><td>After hide, or to reveal a character at the right story moment.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Hide</strong></td><td>Makes the sprite invisible but still running scripts.</td><td>Cutscenes, UI sprites off-stage, or stealth mechanics.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Grow by … %</strong></td><td>Increases sprite size by a step.</td><td>Power-up growth or emphasis before an action.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Shrink by … %</strong></td><td>Decreases sprite size by a step.</td><td>Far-away characters or shrinking power-down.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Change size by … %</strong></td><td>Adds or subtracts from the current size percentage.</td><td>Fine control compared to grow/shrink.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Set size to … %</strong></td><td>Sets size to an exact percentage.</td><td>Normalize size after effects or match two sprites visually.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Switch scene to …</strong></td><td>Loads a specific backdrop/scene from the menu.</td><td>Levels, rooms, weather—pair with Events on backdrop change.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Next scene</strong></td><td>Advances to the next scene in order.</td><td>Linear tours or slideshow-style stories.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Play animation …</strong></td><td>Plays a built-in animation sequence on the sprite.</td><td>Celebrations, hits, or idle loops tied to art assets.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#CF63CF">■</span> Sound</h2><p>Play audio clips attached to your project.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#CF63CF">■</span> <strong>Start sound …</strong></td><td>Starts playing a sound without waiting for it to finish.</td><td>Layered effects or background ambience while motion continues.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#CF63CF">■</span> <strong>Play sound … until done</strong></td><td>Plays a sound and pauses the script until playback ends.</td><td>Short cues where the next action should wait (door slam, success fanfare).</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> Sensing</h2><p>Sensing blocks <strong>ask questions</strong> about the world: input, distance, timers, clones.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Touching … ?</strong></td><td>Reports whether the sprite is touching another sprite or edge.</td><td>Use inside <code>if</code> or <code>wait until</code> for collisions.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Key … pressed?</strong></td><td>Reports whether a key is currently held down.</td><td>Smooth movement while key down, or chord checks.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Mouse down?</strong></td><td>Reports whether the primary mouse button is down.</td><td>Click-and-hold mechanics or painting-style input.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Is a clone?</strong></td><td>True when this script is running on a clone instance.</td><td>Different behavior for clones vs the original sprite.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Mouse x</strong></td><td>Horizontal mouse position on the stage.</td><td>Aim helpers, hover parallax, or custom cursors.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Mouse y</strong></td><td>Vertical mouse position on the stage.</td><td>Pair with mouse x for full pointer tracking.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Distance to …</strong></td><td>Distance to another sprite or point.</td><td>Proximity triggers, difficulty scaling, or “get closer” goals.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Timer</strong></td><td>Seconds since the timer started (floating value).</td><td>Race modes, speed-run HUD, or cooldown math.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Reset timer</strong></td><td>Sets the timer back to zero.</td><td>Start a new lap or phase when an event fires.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> Control</h2><p>Control blocks <strong>pause, repeat, and stop</strong> scripts; clone-related blocks live here too.</p><p><em>Note:</em> <strong>Repeat … times</strong> and <strong>Repeat while / until …</strong> also appear under <strong>Loops</strong> for convenience.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Wait … seconds</strong></td><td>Pauses the script for a number of seconds.</td><td>Timing between lines of dialog, animation beats, or difficulty pacing.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Wait until …</strong></td><td>Pauses until a condition becomes true.</td><td>Wait for collision, key release, or score threshold before continuing.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Repeat … times</strong></td><td>Repeats the enclosed stack a fixed number of times.</td><td>Draw shapes, animate steps, or retry an action N times.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Forever</strong></td><td>Repeats the enclosed stack without stopping.</td><td>Game loops—usually ends with the <strong>Stop …</strong> block or a stop condition inside.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Repeat while / until …</strong></td><td>Repeats while true, or until true, depending on mode.</td><td>Generic Blockly loop; good for “keep going while playing.”</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Repeat … times</strong></td><td>Repeats a stack using a numeric count expression.</td><td>When the count is computed from variables or math blocks.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Stop …</strong></td><td>Stops scripts (this script, other scripts in sprite, or all—per dropdown).</td><td>Game over, level complete, or emergency reset.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>When I start as a clone</strong></td><td>Hat block: runs once for each new clone when it is created.</td><td>Give clones their own behavior (swarm, bullet pattern).</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Create clone of myself</strong></td><td>Creates another instance of this sprite.</td><td>Projectiles, particles, or enemies—pair with clone hat.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Delete this clone</strong></td><td>Removes the current clone (not the original sprite).</td><td>Cleanup when a bullet hits a wall or lifetime expires.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> Logic</h2><p>Decisions, comparisons, and combining true/false values.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>If …</strong></td><td>Runs a stack only if a condition is true; optional else-if branches.</td><td>Score checks, collisions, game states.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>If … else</strong></td><td>Runs one stack if true, another if false.</td><td>Two-way choices without chaining many plain ifs.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>… = ≠ &lt; ≤ &gt; ≥ …</strong></td><td>Compares two values (=, ≠, &lt;, ≤, &gt;, ≥).</td><td>Plug into <code>if</code> and <code>wait until</code>.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>… and or …</strong></td><td>AND / OR of two booleans.</td><td>Combine sensing blocks (key down AND touching goal).</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>Not …</strong></td><td>NOT: flips true/false.</td><td>Invert a condition cleanly.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>True / false</strong></td><td>Constant true or false.</td><td>Defaults or toggles in advanced patterns.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>Null</strong></td><td>Represents an empty / null value (advanced).</td><td>Rare—mostly for library-style patterns.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#4C97FF">■</span> <strong>Test … if true … if false …</strong></td><td>Inline pick: if condition then value A else value B.</td><td>Compact math or text without a full if statement.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> Loops</h2><p>Blockly loop blocks; overlap with Control is intentional so learners find them in either place.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Repeat … times</strong></td><td>Counted repeat using a numeric expression.</td><td>Same block as in Control—use whichever category you open first.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Repeat while / until …</strong></td><td>Loop while or until a condition.</td><td>Matches Control category version.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Count with … from … to … by …</strong></td><td>Loop with a counter variable from start to end by step.</td><td>Grid iteration, draw rows, or index-based logic.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>For each … in list …</strong></td><td>Runs once per item in a list.</td><td>Visit every enemy in a list, or process inventory.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFAB19">■</span> <strong>Break out / continue</strong></td><td>Break out of a loop or continue to next iteration.</td><td>Exit early when a goal is met; skip invalid items.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> Math</h2><p>Numbers, operators, rounding, randomness, and advanced math helpers.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Number</strong></td><td>A numeric literal.</td><td>Plug into motion, waits, comparisons, and variables.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>+ − × ÷ ^</strong></td><td>Add, subtract, multiply, divide, and power.</td><td>Scores, speeds, and formulas.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Abs, sqrt, ln, …</strong></td><td>Single-argument functions: sqrt, abs, neg, ln, log10, exp, etc.</td><td>Normalize values or smooth difficulty.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Sin cos tan …</strong></td><td>sin, cos, tan, asin, acos, atan in degrees.</td><td>Circular motion and waves.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>π, e, …</strong></td><td>Constants such as π and e.</td><td>Geometry and exponentials without memorizing digits.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Even, odd, prime, …</strong></td><td>Checks even/odd, whole, positive, prime, divisible.</td><td>Branching rules and validation.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Round, ceil, floor</strong></td><td>Round, ceil, or floor a value.</td><td>Display scores or snap positions to integers.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Sum, min, max, … of list</strong></td><td>Sum, min, max, average, median, modes, std dev on a list.</td><td>Stats over a collection of scores or times.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Remainder of … ÷ …</strong></td><td>Remainder after division.</td><td>Alternating patterns, wrap-around indexes.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Change … by …</strong></td><td>Adds a value to a numeric variable.</td><td>Shorthand for incrementing counters.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Constrain … low … high …</strong></td><td>Clamps a value between min and max.</td><td>Keep speed or health in safe bounds.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Random integer from … to …</strong></td><td>Random integer between two bounds (inclusive).</td><td>Dice rolls, loot, unpredictable motion.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Random fraction</strong></td><td>Random decimal between 0 and 1 (or configured range per block).</td><td>Jitter, probability checks.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#5CB1D6">■</span> <strong>Atan2 of x: … y: …</strong></td><td>Angle from dy and dx (advanced).</td><td>Point-at-pointer math when built-in point blocks are not enough.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> Text</h2><p>Build and inspect strings; prompt the player for typed input.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Ask … and wait for number</strong></td><td>Prompts the user for a number and returns the value.</td><td>Math games, guesses, or settings chosen by the player.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Text</strong></td><td>A string literal.</td><td>Labels, names, and messages combined with <strong>Join text …</strong>.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Join text …</strong></td><td>Builds text from multiple pieces.</td><td>Personalized messages with names and scores.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Append text …</strong></td><td>Appends text to a string variable.</td><td>Grow a log or story string over time.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Length of …</strong></td><td>Number of characters in a string.</td><td>Validation or pacing typewriter effects.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>… is empty?</strong></td><td>True if the string has no characters.</td><td>Guard before printing optional fields.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>First / last occurrence of text</strong></td><td>Finds first/last position of a substring.</td><td>Parsing simple commands or searching labels.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Letter # in text</strong></td><td>Gets the character at a position.</td><td>Inspect initials or coded strings.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Substring of text</strong></td><td>Extracts part of a string by indices.</td><td>Slice nicknames or drop prefixes.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Uppercase / lowercase / title case</strong></td><td>Upper, lower, or title case.</td><td>Normalize user input for comparisons.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Trim spaces from both sides</strong></td><td>Removes leading/trailing spaces.</td><td>Clean typed input before logic.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Print …</strong></td><td>Prints a line of text to the output/console channel.</td><td>Debugging or simple text-only feedback.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#9966FF">■</span> <strong>Ask for text with prompt …</strong></td><td>Prompts for text and returns the answer (value block).</td><td>Names, passwords (teach care), or free-form quiz answers.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> Lists</h2><p>Ordered collections—create, read, update, sort, and split.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Create list with …</strong></td><td>Builds a list from items (empty or prefilled).</td><td>Start inventories, question banks, or enemy queues.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Create list with item repeated … times</strong></td><td>List filled with one value repeated N times.</td><td>Board grids, placeholders, or default scores.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Length of …</strong></td><td>How many items in the list.</td><td>Loop bounds and win conditions (collect all).</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Is list empty?</strong></td><td>True if the list has zero items.</td><td>End conditions or “any left?” checks.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>First / last index of item in list</strong></td><td>Finds index of an item (first/last).</td><td>Lookup before remove or replace.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Get item from list</strong></td><td>Reads one item by index (from start/end/random).</td><td>Pick next question, random enemy, or first task.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Set / insert item in list</strong></td><td>Writes or inserts at an index.</td><td>Update scoreboard rows or shuffle slots.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Get sublist from list</strong></td><td>Copies a slice of a list.</td><td>Decks, hands, or batched processing.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Split text with delimiter</strong></td><td>Splits text into a list by delimiter.</td><td>CSV-style data or tokenizing words.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FF661A">■</span> <strong>Sort list …</strong></td><td>Sorts a copy (numeric/text, asc/desc).</td><td>Leaderboards or deterministic processing order.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> Color</h2><p>Pick and mix colors for costumes, effects, or logic.</p><table class="ollie-toolbox-guide-table"><thead><tr><th>Toolbox</th><th>What it does</th><th>How to use it</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Color</strong></td><td>Choose a solid color visually.</td><td>Brand colors or art-driven choices.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Random color</strong></td><td>A random color.</td><td>Confetti, disco, or variety.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Color rgb …</strong></td><td>Build a color from red, green, blue (0–255).</td><td>Fade effects or precise brand RGB.</td></tr><tr><td><span style="color:#FFBF00">■</span> <strong>Blend color …</strong></td><td>Blend two colors by a ratio.</td><td>Gradients and smooth transitions.</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><span style="color:#FF8C1A">■</span> Variables</h2><p><strong>Flyout blocks</strong> (Blockly generates these): create a variable, then use <em>get</em>, <em>set</em>, and <em>change by</em> blocks. Color matches the Variables strip (<span style="color:#FF8C1A">■</span>).</p><ul><li><strong>Name variables clearly</strong> (<code>score</code>, <code>lives</code>, <code>speed</code>) so stacks stay readable.</li><li><strong>Use “change by”</strong> for counters instead of long set/get math when possible.</li><li><strong>Scope</strong>: default variables are for this sprite; check Blockly’s scope option if you need a variable shared across sprites (when enabled).</li></ul><h2><span style="color:#FF8C1A">■</span> Variables (dynamic)</h2><p>Same family as Variables, with Blockly’s <strong>dynamic variable</strong> list for advanced projects. Strip color matches Variables (<span style="color:#FF8C1A">■</span>).</p><p>Use when projects have many generated names or plugins add variable types—most lessons use the standard Variables flyout first.</p><h2><span style="color:#FF6680">■</span> Functions</h2><p><strong>My Blocks</strong> flyout: <em>define</em> a function with optional parameters, then call it with a matching block. Color matches the Functions strip (<span style="color:#FF6680">■</span>).</p><ul><li><strong>Deduplicate</strong> repeated stacks (draw a door, reset a level).</li><li><strong>Parameters</strong> let one function draw many sizes or colors.</li><li><strong>Naming</strong> like <code>reset game</code> helps kids find their own blocks quickly.</li></ul>$body$
where id = 'workspace-blocks-reference';
